freenet.io.comm
Interface AsyncMessageCallback

All Known Implementing Classes:
LocationManager.MyCallback, SendMessageOnErrorCallback
public interface AsyncMessageCallback

Callback interface for async message sending.

Method Summary
 void acknowledged()
          Called when the packet is actually acknowledged by the other node.
 void disconnected()
          Called if the node is disconnected while the packet is queued, or after it has been sent.
 void fatalError()
          Called if the packet is lost due to an internal error.
 void sent()
          Called when the packet actually leaves the node.
 

Method Detail

sent

void sent()
Called when the packet actually leaves the node. This DOES NOT MEAN that it has been successfully recieved by the partner node (on a lossy transport).

acknowledged

void acknowledged()
Called when the packet is actually acknowledged by the other node. This is the end of the transaction. On a non-lossy transport this may be called immediately after sent().

disconnected

void disconnected()
Called if the node is disconnected while the packet is queued, or after it has been sent. Terminal.

fatalError

void fatalError()
Called if the packet is lost due to an internal error.
